name: Alexandra Botez
description:
Alexandra Botez is a Canadian chess player and streamer, and the older sister of Andrea Botez.

Update: Retrained from scratch, as this was a very old TI and my process has changed quite a bit since I created it. I think the previous version was good, but probably not as accurate as I would have desired. This new version resembles Alexandra more, I would say. I'm not totally convinced with her hair tonality, but that's easily fixable through prompting. I might revise the dataset in the future to try to solve the issue, but there's just not much good material online of hers, unfortunately.

This version is a 1500-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (4l3xbotez:0.99), a woman with black hair, RAW, close portrait photo, long brown coat, turtleneck, long haircut, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6"

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description: The previous model was quite overtrained, as @epinikion mentioned in his review, so I decided to take a look a it again, review the filewords (I've reached the conclusion that the correct use of commas is fundamental if you mark the "Shuffle tags by ',' when creating prompts" option) and retrain. I interrupted the process at 750 steps, tested the embedding and I gotta say I'm quite satisfied with what I see. It seems both less saturated and probably more accurate than the previous model. Please let me know your impressions!
